Invoking: `validate` with `{'patch': '--- a/clang/lib/Sema/SemaOpenMP.cpp\n+++ b/clang/lib/Sema/SemaOpenMP.cpp\n@@ -2998,10 +2998,17 @@\n static bool finishLinearClauses(Sema &SemaRef, ArrayRef<OMPClause *> Clauses,\n                                 OMPLoopBasedDirective::HelperExprs &B,\n                                 DSAStackTy *Stack) {\n-  assert((SemaRef.CurContext->isDependentContext() || B.builtAll()) &&\n-         "loop exprs were not built");\n-\n-  if (SemaRef.CurContext->isDependentContext())\n-    return false;\n+  if (!SemaRef.CurContext->isDependentContext() && !B.builtAll()) {\n+    // Helper expressions were not built, likely due to earlier error (e.g. invalid collapse argument).\n+    // Bail out early to prevent crashing on null dereference.\n+    return true;\n+  }\n+\n+  if (SemaRef.CurContext->isDependentContext())\n+    return false;\n \n   // Finalize the clauses that need pre-built expressions for CodeGen.\n   for (OMPClause *C : Clauses) {\n     auto *LC = dyn_cast<OMPLinearClause>(C);\n     if (!LC)\n       continue;\n-    if (FinishOpenMPLinearClause(*LC, cast<DeclRefExpr>(B.IterationVarRef),\n-                                 B.NumIterations, SemaRef,\n-                                 SemaRef.getCurScope(), Stack))\n-      return true;\n+    if (FinishOpenMPLinearClause(*LC, cast<DeclRefExpr>(B.IterationVarRef),\n+                                 B.NumIterations, SemaRef,\n+                                 SemaRef.getCurScope(), Stack))\n+      return true;\n   }\n \n   return false;\n }'}`
responded: Based on the ASan report and code inspection, the root cause of the crash is that a malformed OpenMP pragma like `#pragma omp simd collapse(a)` (where `a` is undeclared) causes the OpenMP loop helper expressions (in `OMPLoopBasedDirective::HelperExprs`) not to be built. However, the code in `finishLinearClauses` assumes they are always built and asserts (and then dereferences) them, causing a crash instead of producing a user-facing error about the invalid pragma.

The fix is to harden `finishLinearClauses` and its callers so that if the helper expressions are not built (i.e., `B.builtAll()` is false), we don't try to process linear clauses or dereference null pointers. Instead, we should gracefully error out and let the diagnostic machinery handle the invalid case.

Here is the patch:

```diff
--- a/clang/lib/Sema/SemaOpenMP.cpp
+++ b/clang/lib/Sema/SemaOpenMP.cpp
@@ -2998,10 +2998,17 @@
 static bool finishLinearClauses(Sema &SemaRef, ArrayRef<OMPClause *> Clauses,
                                 OMPLoopBasedDirective::HelperExprs &B,
                                 DSAStackTy *Stack) {
-  assert((SemaRef.CurContext->isDependentContext() || B.builtAll()) &&
-         "loop exprs were not built");
-
-  if (SemaRef.CurContext->isDependentContext())
-    return false;
+  if (!SemaRef.CurContext->isDependentContext() && !B.builtAll()) {
+    // Helper expressions were not built, likely due to earlier error (e.g. invalid collapse argument).
+    // Bail out early to prevent crashing on null dereference.
+    return true;
+  }
+
+  if (SemaRef.CurContext->isDependentContext())
+    return false;

   // Finalize the clauses that need pre-built expressions for CodeGen.
   for (OMPClause *C : Clauses) {
     auto *LC = dyn_cast<OMPLinearClause>(C);
     if (!LC)
       continue;
-    if (FinishOpenMPLinearClause(*LC, cast<DeclRefExpr>(B.IterationVarRef),
-                                 B.NumIterations, SemaRef,
-                                 SemaRef.getCurScope(), Stack))
-      return true;
+    if (FinishOpenMPLinearClause(*LC, cast<DeclRefExpr>(B.IterationVarRef),
+                                 B.NumIterations, SemaRef,
+                                 SemaRef.getCurScope(), Stack))
+      return true;
   }

   return false;
 }
```

This patch checks that the loop helper expressions are built before proceeding, preventing the assertion and null dereference. Now, if the collapse argument is invalid or any other error occurs preventing the construction of helper expressions, the function will return early, allowing the rest of the error reporting machinery to function as intended.

Now, I will validate the patch.

